# Filter Dropdown (Primary Default)

This is the default filter design for ALL modules unless specifically requested otherwise.

## Design Principles
- **Vertical layout**: label on top, selected value below
- **No border on trigger**: clean, borderless button
- **Minimal spacing**: 1px gap between label and value
- **Hover BG**: `#f5f9fe`

## Filter Row Spacing
- Desktop: `gap-5` (20px) between filters
- Mobile: `gap-[15px]` (15px)
- Search widget: `ml-auto` to push right

```tsx
<div className="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-[15px] md:gap-5 items-start md:items-center">
```

## Visual Styling

### Label (Top)
```
text-[12px] text-[#7e7e7e] uppercase tracking-[0.6px] font-semibold
```

### Selected Value (Bottom)
```
text-[14px] text-[#101010] font-semibold
```

### Trigger Button
- `flex items-center gap-2`
- No border/background
- Hover: `hover:bg-[#f5f9fe]`
- Active: `bg-[#f5f9fe]` when open
- Chevron: `size-4`, `rotate-180` when open

### Dropdown Menu
- `absolute top-full left-0 mt-1`
- `bg-white border border-[#e0e0e0] rounded-lg shadow-lg z-10`
- Width varies: Date = 180px, Status = 140px

### Dropdown Options
- `w-full text-left px-4 py-2 text-[14px] text-[#101010]`
- `hover:bg-[#f5f9fe] transition-colors`

## Complete Pattern
```tsx
<div className="flex flex-col gap-[1px]">
  <span className="text-[12px] text-[#7e7e7e] uppercase tracking-[0.6px] font-semibold">
    FILTER NAME
  </span>
  <div className="relative" ref={dropdownRef}>
    <button
      className={`flex items-center gap-2 text-[14px] text-[#101010] font-semibold hover:bg-[#f5f9fe] transition-colors ${isOpen ? "bg-[#f5f9fe]" : ""}`}
      onClick={() => setIsOpen(!isOpen)}
    >
      <span>{selectedValue}</span>
      <ChevronDown className={`size-4 transition-transform ${isOpen ? "rotate-180" : ""}`} />
    </button>
    {isOpen && (
      <div className="absolute top-full left-0 mt-1 bg-white border border-[#e0e0e0] rounded-lg shadow-lg w-[180px] z-10">
        <div className="py-1">
          {options.map(opt => (
            <button key={opt} className="w-full text-left px-4 py-2 text-[14px] text-[#101010] hover:bg-[#f5f9fe] transition-colors" onClick={() => { setSelectedValue(opt); setIsOpen(false); }}>
              {opt}
            </button>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    )}
  </div>
</div>
```

## State Management
- `useState` for selected value + open state
- `useRef` + `useEffect` for click outside detection
- Selecting an option updates value + closes dropdown
